==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Southeast
<hw>South`east"</hw> <pr>(?; <xex>by sailors</xex> sou"-)</pr>,
<pos>n.</pos> <def>The point of the compass equally distant from the
south and the east; the southeast part or region.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Southeast</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Southeast
<hw>South`east</hw> <pr>(?; <xex>by sailors</xex> sou"-)</pr>,
<pos>a.</pos> <def>Of or pertaining to the southeast; proceeding toward,
or coming from, the southeast; <as>as, a <ex>southeast</ex> course; a
<ex>southeast</ex> wind.</as></def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Southeaster</ent>⟦br⟧
